Dataset Description
Customers Table
The Customers table contains customer profile information.
Columns:
Customer ID
Customer Name
City
Account Type
Account Balance
Joining Date
This table helps analyze customer demographics, account types, and balance distribution.
Transactions Table
The Transactions table stores banking transaction information.
Columns:
Transaction ID
Customer ID
Transaction Type (Deposit, Withdrawal, Transfer)
Transaction Amount
Transaction Date
Transaction Status (Success/Fraud)
This table is used to monitor financial transactions and identify suspicious activities.
Database Relationship
The project follows a One-to-Many Relationship.
One customer can perform multiple transactions.
The customer_id in the Customers table acts as the Primary Key.
The customer_id in the Transactions table acts as the Foreign Key.
This relationship allows both tables to be connected using SQL JOIN operations.
