Fraud Detection Logic
The project demonstrates rule-based fraud detection using SQL.
Fraud detection is performed by identifying:
Transactions with Fraud status.
High-value transactions exceeding predefined limits.
Customers involved in suspicious withdrawal patterns.
Customers with unusually high transaction amounts.
High-risk transactions ranked using SQL window functions.
Customer behavior through transaction analysis.
Although this project uses sample data, the SQL logic closely resembles reporting techniques used in banking and financial institutions for fraud monitoring.
